    "recap_headline": "University of Memphis Athletics",
    "recap_text": "NEW ORLEANS, La. \u2013\nThe University of Memphis (6-16, 1-2 American) baseball team dropped the rubber match to Tulane (13-12, 2-1 American), 12-2, Sunday afternoon at Greer Field at Turchin Stadium.\nMemphis recorded seven hits on the day but was unable to keep pace with Tulane's late offensive surge, as the Green Wave scored six runs in the eighth inning to pull away and secure the series win.\nJack Little\nled the Tigers offensively with a 2-for-4 performance, while\nTrae Cassidy\ndrove in a run and\nFreddy Rodriguez\nadded a double and a stolen base.\nOn the mound,\nSeth Impson\nturned in a solid start, allowing just two runs on two hits across 5.0 innings.\nDavis Oswalt\n(1-1) was charged with the loss after surrendering three runs in relief.\nMemphis will return home for a five game homestand beginning Tuesday against Ole Miss. First pitch is scheduled for 6:05 p.m. at FedExPark Avron Fogelman Field.\nHOW IT HAPPENED\nMemphis struck first in the third inning when\nTrae Cassidy\nsingled to left field to score\nFreddy Rodriguez\n, giving the Tigers a 1-0 lead.\nTulane answered in the fourth, plating two runs on an RBI double and a single to take a 2-1 advantage.\nThe Tigers evened the game in the sixth as\nCade Hitson\nlaid down a sacrifice bunt to bring home\nTyler Harrington\n, tying the score at 2-2.\nThe Green Wave regained control in the bottom of the sixth, capitalizing on a Memphis error and timely hitting to score three runs and take a 5-2 lead.\nTulane added another run in the seventh before breaking the game open in the eighth with a six-run frame to extend the lead to 12-2 and end the game in run-rule fashion.\nNOTABLES\nFreddy Rodriguez\nstole a base for the Tigers, bringing the team's season total to 47 steals, which ranks in the top 40 nationally.\nRodriguez is 14-16 on the year.\nHis 14 stolen bases are third-most in the conference.\nStarting pitcher\nSeth Impson\ndelivered his best outing of the year so far.\nImpson threw 87 pitches over 5 innings while allowing two runs on just two hits and added two strikeouts.\nHis 5 innings pitched, two runs allowed and two hits allowed are all career-bests at the D1 level.\nLeft fielder\nJack Little\nwent 2-for-4 at the plate.\nCollected his fourth multi-hit game of the season.\nAfter a single on Sunday, second baseman\nShane Cox\ncontinued his streak of reaching base safely in every game thus far.\nCox has recorded at least one hit in 19 of 22 games this season.\nCox leads the Tigers in batting average (.352), hits (31), doubles (9), and extra-base hits (12).\nSCORING SUMMARY\nTop 3:\nTrae Cassidy\nsingled,\nFreddy Rodriguez\nscored.\nMemphis 1, Tulane 0\nBottom 4:\nMatthias Haas doubled, Jason Wachs scored.\nTrent Liolios singled, Matthias Haas scored.\nMemphis 1, Tulane 2\nTop 6:\nCade Hitson\nhit a sacrifice bunt,\nTyler Harrington\nscored.\nMemphis 2, Tulane 2\nBottom 6:\nNate Johnson doubled, Tye Wood scored on a fielding error.\nJack Johnson hit a sacrifice fly, Nate Johnson scored.\nHugh Pinkney singled, Matthias Haas scored.\nMemphis 2, Tulane 5\nBottom 7:\nTye Wood caught stealing, Jason Wachs scored.\nMemphis 2, Tulane 6\nBottom 8:\nTye Wood hit by pitch, Hugh Pinkney scored.\nNate Johnson doubled, Kaikea Harrison and Jason Wachs scored.\nEvan Burg reached on a throwing error, Tye Wood scored.\nTrent Liolios doubled, Evan Burg scored, unearned.\nMemphis 2, Tulane 12\nUP NEXT\nThe Tigers will be back in action on Tuesday, March 24, at FedExPark Avron Fogelman Field when they take on Ole Miss. First pitch is set for 6:05 p.m.\nHOW TO FOLLOW THE TIGERS:\nFor complete information on\u00a0Memphis Tiger Baseball, visit\nwww.GoTigersGo.com\nand follow the team's social media channels on\nTwitter\n,\nInstagram\nand\nFacebook\n.",
